eight:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"></pre>\n"]},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["The email addresses the recipient by name, 'Carlos', ensuring personalization. It is concise, containing 49 words, well under the 150-word limit. The tone is professional throughout, welcoming the new employee and expressing excitement. However, while the content aligns with the input details, it could have included a direct reference to the company size or industry for further relevance.\n","[0.7404426911651816, 0.9060396473372896, 0.9588622644650917, 0.9041980108449229, 0.6037905404137641, 0.9282217819396447]\n","icp_fit exact match rate: 0.3333333333333333\n","email avg score: 0.8402591560276491\n"]}],"source":["import json\n","\n","icp_fit_scores = []\n","email_scores = []\n","\n","for ex in examples:\n","    input = ex.inputs\n","    result = agent.invoke(input)\n","\n","    actual = result[\"structured_response\"]\n","    expected = ex.outputs[\"outputs_1\"]\n","\n","    icp_fit_tc = LLMTestCase(\n","        input=json.dumps(input),\n","        actual_output=actual.icp_fit,\n","        expected_output=expected.get(\"icp_fit\", \"\"),\n","    )\n","    icp_fit_evaluator.measure(icp_fit_tc)\n","    icp_fit_scores.append(icp_fit_evaluator.score)\n","\n","\n","    email_tc = LLMTestCase(\n","        input=json.dumps(input),\n","        actual_output=actual.body,\n","        expected_output=expected.get(\"body\", \"\"),\n","    )\n","    email_evaluator.measure(email_tc)\n","    email_scores.append(email_evaluator.score)\n","    print(email_evaluator.reason)\n","\n","print(email_scores)\n","\n","avg = sum(email_scores) / len(email_scores);\n","\n","print(\"icp_fit exact match rate:\", sum(icp_fit_scores) / len(icp_fit_scores))\n","print(\"email avg score:\", sum(email_scores) / len(email_scores))"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"d815cb96","metadata":{"id":"d815cb96"},"source":["---\n","## Step 3: Online Evaluation on LangSmith\n","\n","Online eval scores **production traces** in real time. We'll set up rules in LangSmith that automatically evaluate every run.\n","\n","### In the LangSmith UI:\n","\n","1. Go to your **default** project\n","2. Click **Tracing** → **default** → **New** → **New Evaluator**\n","3. Create a Prebuilt Evaluator\n","\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"c90d9786","metadata":{"id":"c90d9786"},"source":["### Run agent on a new input"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"84286ed2","metadata":{"id":"84286ed2","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1778791472539,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":4418,"user":{"displayName":"Vijay Misra","userId":"00234019357047153423"}},"outputId":"2ce050dd-8d4b-414e-c724-7b5dce0b0770"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["ICP Fit:  low\n","Reason:   The email domain appears to be from a disposable or spam-related service, indicating low potential for meaningful engagement.\n","Subject:  Welcome to Glop, Whatever you want!\n"]}],"source":["result = agent.invoke({\n","    \"messages\": [{\n","        \"role\": \"user\",\n","        \"content\": \"\"\"Process this signup:\n","        email: unknown@spam.com\n","        first_name: Whatever you want\n","        \"\"\"\n","    }]\n","})\n","\n","# Extract structured response\n","output = result[\"structured_response\"]\n","print(f\"ICP Fit:  {output.icp_fit}\")\n","print(f\"Reason:   {output.reason}\")\n","print(f\"Subject:  {output.subject}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"e6a6118c","metadata":{"id":"e6a6118c"},"source":["### Check Online Evaluation Scores\n","\n","Go back to [LangSmith](https://smith.langchain.com) → **default** project.\n","\n","You should now see:\n","- ✅ A new trace from the last run\n","- ✅ **Feedback** attached to that trace\n","\n","\n","### What to look for:\n","1. Filter by feedback score to find failed cases\n","2. Click into failing traces to understand **why** they failed\n","3. Look at the **Monitor** tab for quality metrics"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"027dd2c7","metadata":{"id":"027dd2c7"},"source":["---\n","## Step 4: Add Online Eval Failures to the Golden Dataset\n","\n","This is the production feedback loop: when online eval catches a bad output, you add that case to your golden dataset so offline eval catches it next time.\n","\n","### In the LangSmith UI (recommended):\n","\n","1. Find a trace that **failed** an online eval rule (or that you manually identify as wrong)\n","2. Click on the trace → **Add to Dataset**\n","3. Select **golden-dataset**\n","4. Fill in the **expected output**\n","5. Your golden dataset now has one more case — sourced from a real production failure"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"24585c2c","metadata":{"id":"24585c2c"},"source":["### The production feedback loop\n","\n","```\n","┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n","│                                                 │\n","│   Agent runs on new signups                     │\n","│        │                                        │\n","│        ▼                                        │\n","│   LangSmith traces + online eval scores         │\n","│        │                                        │\n","│        ▼                                        │\n","│   Failures flagged automatically                │\n","│        │                                        │\n","│        ▼                                        │\n","│   Add failing cases to golden dataset           │\n","│        │                                        │\n","│        ▼                                        │\n","│   Re-run offline eval (DeepEval) with           │\n","│   expanded golden set                           │\n","│        │                                        │\n","│        ▼                                        │\n","│   Fix prompt / agent → redeploy                 │\n","│        │                                        │\n","│        └──────────── loop ──────────────────────┘\n","│                                                 │\n","└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n","```\n","\n","This is the core LLMOps pattern: **online eval catches issues → golden dataset grows → offline eval prevents regressions → agent improves.**"]}],"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.11.0"},"colab":{"provenance":[{"file_id":"1uSM0yIZ35_vY-brALKeZbLEoZx9ndANy","timestamp":1778796921693},{"file_id":"1C_lrBGx3iDhGcB6a3rDo-8p5_U5EgjDB","timestamp":1778436630871},{"file_id":"1LDGkZWrEAxILUZUS1HhNQ54vW-OEZOl8","timestamp":1774321720979}]},"widgets":{"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-state+json":{"63e39aba11d44bce90165eb2151cfd8f":{"model_module":"@jupyter-widgets/output","model_name":"OutputModel","model_module_version":"1.0.0","state":{"_dom_classes":[],"_model_module":"@jupyter-widgets/output","_model_module_version":"1.0.0","_model_name":"OutputModel","_view_count":null,"_view_module":"@jupyter-widgets/output","_view_module_version":"1.0.0","_view_name":"OutputView","layout":"IPY_MODEL_3a53f16d836741d4a2860265d54719d8","msg_id":"","outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"\u001b[38;2;106;0;255m⠋\u001b[0m \u001b[38;5;237m━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m ✨ You're running DeepEval's latest \u001b[38;2;106;0;255mExact Match Metric\u001b[0m! \u001b[38;2;55;65;81m(using None, strict=False, async_mode=True)...\u001b[0m\n","text/html":"<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"><span style=\"color: #6a00ff; text-decoration-color: #6a00ff\">⠋</span> <span style=\"color: #3a3a3a; text-decoration-color: #3a3a3a\">━━━━━━━━━━</span> ✨ You're running DeepEval's latest <span style=\"color: #6a00ff; text-decoration-color: #6a00ff\">Exact Match Metric</span>! <span style=\"color: #374151; text-decoration-color: #374151